{"sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/variantref\/normalform"]}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"extendedModule":"GLib","title":"normalForm","role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Instance Property","fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"normalForm","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib10VariantRefV","text":"VariantRef","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib15VariantProtocolPAAE10normalFormAA0B3RefVSgvp::SYNTHESIZED::s:4GLib10VariantRefV","symbolKind":"property"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantRef","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantRef\/VariantProtocol-Implementations"]]},"abstract":[{"text":"Gets a ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant"},{"type":"text","text":" instance that has the same value as "},{"code":"value","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"trusted to be in normal form.","type":"text"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantRef\/normalForm"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"normalForm"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib10VariantRefV","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"VariantRef"},{"kind":"text","text":"! { "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"get"},{"text":" }","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"value"},{"type":"text","text":" is already trusted to be in normal form then a new"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"reference to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"value"},{"type":"text","text":" is returned."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"code":"value","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is not already trusted, then it is scanned to check if it","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"is in normal form.  If it is found to be in normal form then it is"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"marked as trusted and a new reference to it is returned.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"value"},{"text":" is found not to be in normal form then a new trusted","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant"},{"text":" is created with the same value as ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"value"},{"type":"text","text":". The non-normal parts of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"value"},{"text":" will be replaced with default values which are guaranteed to be in","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"normal form."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It makes sense to call this function if you’ve received "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","isActive":true},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"data from untrusted sources and you want to ensure your serialized"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"output is definitely in normal form."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"value"},{"text":" is already in normal form, a new reference will be returned","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(which will be floating if ","type":"text"},{"code":"value","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is floating). If it is not in normal form,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the newly created "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" will be returned with a single non-floating"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"reference. Typically, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_variant_take_ref()"},{"type":"text","text":" should be called on the return"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"value from this function to guarantee ownership of a single non-floating","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"reference to it.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/VariantRef/VariantProtocol-Implementations":{"role":"collectionGroup","kind":"article","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/variantref\/variantprotocol-implementations","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantRef\/VariantProtocol-Implementations","title":"VariantProtocol Implementations"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"kind":"symbol","role":"collection","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","title":"GLib","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/Variant":{"type":"topic","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/variant","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","kind":"symbol","title":"Variant","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Variant","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Variant","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"code":"GVariant","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is a variant datatype; it can contain one or more values","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"along with information about the type of the values.","type":"text"}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/G